node: close | Gentle Hands Bevin
  *(Gentle Hands Bevin bends back over his crowded desk of inks and seals — forging manumissions and pardons and the dead's last loving words, freeing everyone the law wrongs and unable to write the one pardon he needs for himself — and whether you helped him see his forgeries as justice the world left unrecorded, or let him keep his tired humility, you carry away the underworld's kindest paradox: that in a world whose laws are fences built by the powerful, the most honest hand in the quarter is the one that lies for a living — and that the document the condemned dead truly need is not a forged pardon at all, but a voice loud enough to say the gate was never guarded.)*

# ─── 103 ─── The Thief Who Steals Memories ───
conversation: npc.guild.memthief | The Memory-Thief
node: 0 | A Thief of a Stranger Sort
  *(A slight figure sits very still in the corner of the safehouse, and there is something *crowded* about them — as though the single body holds far more than one life's worth of remembering. Their eyes are kind and unbearably full. When they look at you, you have the uncanny sense they are seeing not just you but everyone you resemble, everyone whose memories they carry who once looked as you look now.)* You're whole. *(quietly, with a faint ache.)* I can tell, you know. The *whole* ones walk differently. Lighter. *(they gesture to a seat.)* Sit, if you like. I won't take anything. I only take what's *offered* — *begged*, usually. That's my trade. I'm the one they come to when a memory is *killing* them, and they *can't* live with it, and they want it — *gone.* I take it. I'm good at it. *(their full eyes meet yours.)* The trouble is where it *goes.*
  enter: SET npc.memthief_met
  auto: 1
node: 1 | The Memory-Thief
  *(They press a hand to their own chest, as though to feel the crowd inside.)* They come to me *broken.* *(quietly.)* A mother who watched her child *drown* and can't *stop* *seeing* it. A soldier who can't *close* his *eyes* without the *field.* A woman whose *husband's* *last* *cruelty* *poisons* every *good* memory she has of him. *(their voice is gentle.)* And they *beg* me: *"take it. Cut it out. I don't care what it costs, I cannot* live *with this picture behind my eyes."* *(they meet your gaze.)* And I *can.* That's my *gift*, my *curse* — I can *reach* in and *lift* a memory *clean* away, and the *mother* *stops* *seeing* the *drowning*, the *soldier* *sleeps*, the *widow* gets her *husband* *back* *unpoisoned.* They *weep* with *relief.* They walk out *lighter.* *Whole.* *(their full eyes lower.)* But a memory doesn't *vanish* when I *lift* it. It has to *go* *somewhere.* And it goes — *(they touch their chest again)* — *here.* *Into* *me.* I *carry* the *drowning* now. *And* the *field.* *And* the *husband's* *cruelty.* *Every* memory I've *ever* *taken* as a *mercy*, I *hold*, *all* of them, *all* at *once*, and I *cannot* *put* *them* *down*, because there's *no one* *I* can *go* to — *no* *memory-thief* for the *memory-thief.* *(quietly.)* I am a *museum* of *other* people's *worst* *moments.* I *ease* *everyone* and *fill* *myself*, and I have *eased* so *many* that I can *barely* *find* my *own* *life* *anymore* under the *crowd* of *borrowed* *agonies.* *(they look at you.)* It's a *good* *trade.* A *kind* one. It's *killing* me *slower* than the *memories* were *killing* *them.* I tell myself that's a *fair* *exchange.* *Most* days I *believe* it.
  * [INSIGHT 18] "You think taking the memory is the only mercy — cut it out, carry it yourself. But the mother who watched her child drown didn't need the memory *gone.* She needed it *bearable.* You've been performing amputations when what they needed was *healing* — and paying for it with your own self. There's a mercy that doesn't require you to become a tomb." -> bearable ?? weary
  * "Every memory you carry was given to you in trust — a stranger's worst moment, handed over because they couldn't hold it. You're not a museum of agonies. You're the most loaded *witness* in the world: you hold the drowning so the mother doesn't have to, and that means the child is still *remembered*, by someone, even if not by her." -> witness
  * "You said there's no memory-thief for the memory-thief. But I'm here, and I'm listening, and a memory *spoken* to someone who receives it is a memory *shared* — not lifted, not stolen, just... carried by two. You can't put them down. But maybe you don't have to hold every one of them *alone.*" -> shared | fx appr.naeve +3
  * "How much of *you* is left, under the crowd? Somewhere in there is the person you were before the first theft — your own memories, your own life. If I asked you to tell me *one* thing that's truly yours, not borrowed from a client, could you find it?" -> yours | fx appr.ilfaeril +2
node: bearable | The Memory-Thief
  *(They go very still, and their unbearably full eyes fill further.)* ...Bearable, not gone. *(barely a whisper.)* *(they press both hands to their chest.)* I have *never* — in *all* the years, *all* the *thefts* — *considered* that there was *another* *door.* *(their voice shakes.)* They come *begging* *"take it away,"* and I *take* it *away*, because that's what they *ask* and that's what I *can* *do* — but you're saying the *mother* didn't *truly* want the *drowning* *gone.* *(slowly.)* If it were *gone* — *truly* — she'd *lose* the *child.* The *drowning* is *terrible*, but it's *also* the *last* *time* she *saw* her *little* one's *face*, the *last* *moment* they *existed*, and to *cut* it *out* *clean* is to *cut* out — *(their breath catches)* — *the child.* *(they meet your eyes.)* I've been *amputating* *love* to *stop* *pain*, because they *came* to *me* in *too* *much* *agony* to *tell* the *difference*, and I *was* *too* *proud* of my *gift* to *ask* if there was a *gentler* *cut.* *(their voice fills.)* A *memory* made *bearable* — *held*, *witnessed*, *wept* over with *someone*, *softened* over *time* — *keeps* the *child* *and* *eases* the *mother.* But it *takes* *longer.* It takes *sitting* *with* her, *helping* her *carry* it, instead of *lifting* it *clean* and *walking* away *full.* *(they look at their own crowded chest.)* I chose the *fast* mercy. The *amputation.* Because it *worked* *immediately* and made them *weep* with *relief* and made *me* feel like a *healer.* *(quietly.)* And it's *filled* me with *agonies* that *never* *needed* to be *removed* at *all* — *only* *held*, *gently*, by *someone* *beside* the *grieving*, *until* they *softened.* *(they meet your eyes.)* I could *learn* that. The *slower* mercy. It would *empty* me, in *time* — *and* it would *let* the *mother* *keep* her *child's* *face.* *Both.* *Teach* me to *stop* *amputating.* I've been a *tomb* when I could have been a *companion.*
  enter: SET npc.memthief_bearable, SET act5.witness_then_release, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
  auto: close
node: witness | The Memory-Thief
  *(Their crowded eyes widen, and for a moment the weight in them shifts from burden toward something almost like purpose.)* The most loaded witness in the world. *(slowly.)* *(they press a hand to their chest.)* I've *carried* them as — as a *junkyard.* A *dumping* *ground.* *Other* *people's* *refuse*, *piled* in *me*, *rotting.* *(their voice catches.)* But you're saying — every one was *handed* to me in *trust.* *(they close their eyes.)* The *mother's* *drowning.* When I *took* it, I *thought* I *robbed* it from her. But you're saying I *received* it — *"hold this, I cannot, please" * — and that means the *child* who *drowned* is *still* *remembered.* *By me.* The *mother* *can't* bear to *hold* her *little* one's *last* *moment*, but it *isn't* *lost*, because *I* *hold* it, *witness* it, *keep* the *child* *real* in the *one* place that *can* *bear* it. *(their full eyes open, streaming.)* I'm not a *museum* of *agonies.* I'm an — an *ark.* *(quietly, astonished.)* *Every* *worst* *moment* I *carry* is *also* a *person*, *kept*, *witnessed*, *un-forgotten*, *because* I *agreed* to *hold* what their *loved* *ones* *couldn't.* The *soldier's* *field* is *full* of *men* who *died*, and *I* *remember* them, *all* of them, when *no* *one* *else* *can* *bear* to. *(they meet your eyes.)* That's — that *changes* the *weight.* It's *still* *heavy.* But it's not *garbage* I'm *cursed* to *hold.* It's a *thousand* *people* *the* *world* *would* have *forgotten*, *kept* *real* in the *one* *heart* *strong* enough to *carry* their *worst* *day.* *(quietly.)* I'm the *Wall's* *opposite*, *aren't* I. The *Wall* *keeps* the *forgotten* to *erase* them. I *keep* them to *remember* them. *Same* *holding.* *Opposite* *love.*
  enter: SET npc.memthief_witness, SET act2.cataloguing_defeats_the_wall, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.ilfaeril +5
  auto: close
node: shared | The Memory-Thief
  *(They look at you for a long, still moment, and their crowded eyes fill with something they clearly haven't let themselves feel in years: the possibility of relief.)* No memory-thief for the memory-thief. *(quietly.)* That's been — the *loneliest* *fact* of my *life.* *(their hands tremble.)* *Everyone* comes to *me* to be *eased*, and there's *no* *one* — *no* *one* — for *me*, because my *gift* doesn't *work* on *myself*, and *no* *other* of my *kind* *lives* *near*, and *who* would *take* a *thief's* *crowded* *agonies* and *carry* *them*? *(they meet your eyes.)* But you're not *offering* to *take* them. *(slowly.)* You're offering to — *hear* them. *(their breath catches.)* To *let* me *speak* one — *one* of the *thousand* — *aloud*, to a *person* who *receives* it, so that it's not *lifted* from me, not *stolen*, just — *shared.* *Held* by *two.* *(quietly, wondering.)* I don't — I've *never* *tried* that. I *take* and I *carry* and I *hold*, *alone*, because *holding-alone* is the *whole* *shape* of *what* I *am.* *(they press a hand to their chest.)* But a memory *spoken* and *received* — it doesn't *leave* me, but it stops being *only* *mine* to *bear.* *(their full eyes stream.)* Will you — *(their voice shakes)* — there's a *child.* A *drowning.* I've held it *eleven* *years.* The *mother* *gave* it me and *walked* away *light* and I have *never*, *not* *once*, *told* it to *another* *living* *soul.* *(they meet your eyes.)* *Let* me *tell* you about the *child.* Not to *give* her to you. Just so that, after *eleven* years, the *drowning* is held by *someone* *beside* me. So I'm not the *only* one who *remembers* her *face.* *(quietly.)* That's — that's a *mercy* I *never* knew *existed.* The *one* I *give* *everyone* *else*, *finally*, *given* to *me.* Not *taken.* *Shared.*
  enter: SET npc.memthief_shared, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
  auto: close
node: yours | The Memory-Thief
  *(The question stops them, and a flicker of something like panic crosses their crowded face — and then, slowly, with great effort, they reach *past* the borrowed agonies for something underneath.)* One thing that's truly mine. *(quietly.)* *(they close their eyes, searching.)* That's — that's *harder* than you *know.* I've *carried* so *many* *lives* that my *own* has gone — *quiet.* *Buried.* I *reach* for a *memory* and I'm *not* *sure*, *anymore*, if it's *mine* or a *client's* — did *I* *love* on a *riverbank*, or did I *take* that *from* a *widow?* Was *that* *my* *mother's* *voice*, or a *gift* from a *grieving* *son?* *(their voice shakes.)* The *crowd* has — *blurred* the *edges* of *me.* *(but they keep *searching*, and slowly, a small, certain light comes into their face.)* ...There's a *bird.* *(quietly.)* When I was *small* — *before* the *gift*, *before* the *first* *theft* — there was a *bird* that came to my *window*, a *common* *grey* *thing*, and I *fed* it *crumbs*, and it *came* *back*, *every* *morning*, for a *whole* *summer*, and it was *mine*, just *mine*, a *small* *ordinary* *joy* that *no* *client* *ever* *gave* me because it's *too* *small* and *too* *happy* to *be* a *memory* *anyone* *begs* to *lose.* *(their eyes open, wet and amazed.)* *That's* *mine.* The *bird.* The *crumbs.* The *summer.* *(they press it to their chest like treasure.)* I'd *forgotten* I had *anything* that was *only* *mine* and *only* *good.* *(they meet your eyes.)* Thank you. You've — you've *handed* me back the *one* *memory* the *crowd* *couldn't* *bury*, because it was *too* *small* to *matter* to *anyone* but *me.* *(quietly.)* I'm *still* in *here.* Under the *thousand* *agonies.* There's a *child* who *fed* a *grey* *bird.* That's — that's *enough* to *start* *finding* my *way* *back.*
  enter: SET npc.memthief_yours, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.ilfaeril +4
  auto: close
node: weary | The Memory-Thief
  *(They shake their head slowly, the weight in their eyes too heavy to lift toward hope.)* It's a *kind* *thought.* *(quietly.)* *"A gentler mercy," "a slower cut."* *(they press a hand to their crowded chest.)* But they come to me *drowning*, *friend.* In *too* *much* *agony* to *wait* for a *slow* *healing.* They *need* it *gone* *tonight*, before they *hang* themselves, before they *drink* the *poison*, and I — I *take* it, *fast*, because *fast* is what *saves* them, and *slow* might be *kinder* but the *dead* *can't* *heal* *slowly.* *(their full eyes lower.)* So I'll *keep* *taking.* *Keep* *filling.* It's *killing* me, *yes*, but it *un-kills* *them*, *tonight*, *which* is *when* they *need* it. *(quietly.)* Maybe there *is* a *gentler* *way.* But I *haven't* *the* *time* to *learn* it, *standing* *between* a *broken* *person* and a *rope.* *(they look away.)* Go on. *Leave* the *thief* to the *crowd.* It's *what* I'm *for.* *Someone* has to *hold* the *unholdable*, and it *might* as *well* be the *one* who *can.* *(and they sit, very still, in the corner of the safehouse, holding a thousand borrowed agonies alone, too weighed-down to reach for the mercy they give everyone but themselves.)*
  auto: close
node: close | The Memory-Thief
  *(The memory-thief sits very still in the corner of the safehouse — a slight figure crowded with a thousand borrowed agonies, easing the broken by lifting their worst moments into a self that can never set them down — and whether you taught them the slower mercy of making a memory bearable instead of gone, or named them the ark rather than the junkyard of the forgotten, or simply received one stolen drowning so it was no longer carried alone, you carry away the strangest echo of the Wall in the whole underworld: that there is a kind of keeping that erases and a kind that remembers, that they can look identical from outside, and that the whole difference is whether the holder loves what they hold.)*

# ─── 104 ─── The Spymaster Who's Lost Track of Which Side She's On ───
conversation: npc.guild.spymaster | The Spymaster
node: 0 | A Woman of Many Faces
  *(She could be anyone — and that, you realize, is precisely the problem. The woman across the table has the relaxed, attentive blankness of someone wearing a face that isn't quite hers, over another that isn't quite hers either, all the way down. She pours two cups of wine and slides one toward you with a smile calibrated to put you at ease, and you cannot tell a single true thing about her, and you suspect neither can she.)* You're wondering which of us is being played. *(a pleasant smile.)* Wise. The answer, usually, is *both.* *(she sips.)* They call me a *spymaster.* I prefer *clearing-house.* Secrets in, secrets out, every faction in the Gate paying me for the *other* factions' whispers. *(her smile flickers, almost imperceptibly.)* I've worn so many *colors* that I — *(she pauses, a half-second too long)* — that I keep them all *very* organized. *Very.* Sit. Tell me nothing true. It's restful, for me, when no one does.
  enter: SET npc.spymaster_met
  auto: 1
node: 1 | The Spymaster
  *(She turns her cup slowly, and the practiced ease frays at the edges as she talks, like a mask worn thin.)* I have served — let me see if I can *count* — the *Flaming Fist*, by feeding them the *Guild's* movements. The *Guild*, by feeding them the *Fist's.* The *Harpers*, the *Choir*, two *rival* *dukes*, a *Calishite* *cabal*, and — for a *memorable* *season* — *all* of them *at once*, each *believing* I was *theirs.* *(a thin smile.)* It's *good* work. *Lucrative.* I'm *very* good at it. The *trick* is to *become*, *fully*, *whoever* you're *speaking* to — to *believe*, in the *moment*, that you *are* the *Fist* loyalist, the *Guild* woman, the *Harper* idealist — because a *lie* you *believe* is *undetectable.* *(her cup stills.)* And I've *believed* so *many* *loyalties*, so *fully*, *one* after *another*, for *so* *many* *years*, that — *(the practiced ease finally cracks)* — that I have *lost* the *thread* of which one was ever *mine.* *(quietly.)* I started *somewhere.* I *know* I did. There was a — a *reason*, a *cause*, a *side* I *began* on, *before* the *masks*, that *all* the *other* masks were *in service of.* And I *cannot* *find* it *anymore.* I've *been* the *Fist* and the *Guild* and the *Harper* so *convincingly*, so *often*, that the *original* face — the *real* allegiance, the *thing* I was *protecting* by *wearing* all the *others* — has *worn* away, like a *coin* *handled* too *long.* *(she meets your eyes, and for a flicker there's something genuinely lost in them.)* I'm *very* good at knowing what *everyone* *else* *is.* I have *no* idea, *anymore*, what *I* am. The *masks* ate the *face.* And I can't even be *sure* this — *this* *confession*, *right* now — isn't *just* *another* one.
  * [INSIGHT 18] "You say the masks ate the face — but you just told me a true thing, and it cost you something to say it. That's the thread. Not a faction. The original loyalty was never to a side. It was to a *person*, or a *promise* — something small enough that no mask could be built over it. Who were you protecting, before the colors? Find *them*, and you find you." -> person ?? mask
  * "Here's a possibility that'll unsettle you: maybe you never lost your true side. Maybe you discovered, mask by mask, that *none* of them deserved the loyalty — Fist, Guild, Harper, all using people as currency — and the 'lost thread' is just the grief of learning there was no side worth being true to. The emptiness isn't confusion. It's *disillusionment.*" -> disillusion
  * "You can't tell if this confession is another mask. Then let's test it: a mask is worn to *gain* something. What do you gain by telling me you're lost? Nothing — it's pure liability. Which means it's the one thing you've said that *can't* be a play. The lostness is real. Start building from there." -> test | fx appr.roen +2
  * "I walk with someone who wears faces for a living too — Roen. But Roen keeps one thing un-masked, a core nobody gets to play. You filed *everything*, kept nothing back, and that's why you're hollow. It's not too late to wall off one true room. What would you put in it?" -> room | fx appr.roen +3
node: person | The Spymaster
  *(She goes utterly still, and the relaxed blankness drops entirely, and underneath is a face that is, for the first time, *only* one face — frightened, and searching.)* ...A person. *(barely a whisper.)* Not a *side.* *(her hand trembles on the cup.)* I've been *looking* for the *wrong* *thing.* All these *years* I've *asked* *"which faction was I truly loyal to,"* and I *couldn't* *find* it because — because there *wasn't* one, the *factions* were *all* *masks*, *every* one, *worn* over — *(her breath catches.)* — over *something* *smaller.* *(she closes her eyes, searching.)* There was a — *(slowly, like surfacing from deep water)* — a *sister.* *Younger.* *Sick.* And the *medicine* she needed cost more than an *honest* life *could* *earn*, and so I — I took the *first* *mask*, *spied* for the *first* *coin*, *to* *pay* for *her* *care.* *(her eyes open, wet.)* *That* was the *thread.* Not the *Fist*, not the *Guild* — *Lira.* My *sister.* *Every* *mask* I *ever* *wore* was, at the *start*, *in* *service* of *keeping* *Lira* *alive*, and I *wore* so *many*, for *so* *long*, that I *forgot* the *girl* the *whole* *masquerade* was *for.* *(her voice breaks.)* She — she *died*, *years* ago. The *medicine* *bought* her *time*, *not* a *cure.* And when she *died*, the *reason* for the *masks* *died* with her, but I *kept* *wearing* them, because by *then* I *didn't* *know* how to *stop*, and there was *no* *face* *left* *underneath* to *go* *back* to. *(she meets your eyes.)* *Lira.* That's *me.* Not a *spy* for *anyone.* A *sister* who *started* *lying* to *save* a *girl* and *forgot*, *somewhere* in the *thousand* *lies*, that the *girl* was the *only* *truth.* *(quietly.)* Thank you for *asking* *who* instead of *which.* I've been *lost* in the *sides.* The *answer* was a *name.* It *always* was.
  enter: SET npc.spymaster_person, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.roen +5
  auto: close
node: disillusion | The Spymaster
  *(She tilts her head, and a slow, dangerous recognition moves across her face.)* Disillusionment, not confusion. *(quietly.)* *(she sets down the cup.)* You think the *emptiness* isn't a *thread* I *lost* — it's a *truth* I *found.* *(she's very still.)* That I wore the *Fist's* face and saw, *up* *close*, that the *Fist* *burns* *villages.* Wore the *Guild's* and saw it *bleeds* the *poor.* Wore the *Harper's* and saw that *even* the *idealists* *spend* *people* like *coin* for the *"greater good."* *(her voice hardens.)* And that the *"lost thread"* I've been *grieving* is *really* the *discovery* that — *(she stops, and the practiced blankness cracks)* — that there was *never* a *side* *worth* being *true* to. *That* the *reason* I *can't* *find* my *original* *loyalty* is *not* that I *forgot* it, but that *every* *time* I got *close* *enough* to a *faction* to *see* its *heart*, the *heart* was *rotten*, and my *loyalty* *died* *there*, *quietly*, *mask* by *mask.* *(she meets your eyes, and there's something raw in it.)* That's — *gods*, that's *worse* than *confusion*, and *truer.* I'm not a *woman* who *lost* her *cause.* I'm a *woman* who *auditioned* *every* *cause* and found them *all* *wanting*, and the *hollowness* is just — *what's* *left* when you've *seen* behind *every* mask, *including* the ones the *factions* *wear* to *fool* *themselves.* *(quietly.)* The *masks* didn't eat my *face.* They *showed* me there was *nothing* *worth* *being* *loyal* *to*, and a *person* with *nothing* *worth* *loyalty* *becomes* — *this.* A *clearing-house.* *(she looks at you.)* So *what* *do* I *do*, knowing *no* *side* *deserves* me? *(a thin, lost smile.)* That's *not* a *spy's* *question. That's a* soul's. *And I haven't worn that face in* years.*
  enter: SET npc.spymaster_disillusion, SET act2.wall_has_no_author, appr.ilfaeril +4
