node: test | The Spymaster
  *(She pauses — and then a genuine, surprised laugh escapes her, the first thing she's done that doesn't seem calculated.)* What do I *gain* by telling you I'm lost. *(she turns it over, the spy in her examining her own play.)* ...*Nothing.* *(slowly.)* You're *right.* A *mask* is *worn* to *gain* — *trust*, *information*, *advantage* — and *"I am hollow and have lost my true self"* gains me — *(she frowns)* — *nothing.* It's *pure* *liability.* It *tells* a *stranger* my *deepest* *weakness*, *hands* you a *blade* you could *sell* to *any* of my *six* *employers*, and *gets* me *not* *one* *thing* in *return.* *(she meets your eyes, and something steadies.)* Which means — by my *own* *trade's* *logic* — it *can't* *be* a *play.* *(quietly, wondering.)* I've been *so* *afraid* that *everything* I *say* is *another* *mask* that I *couldn't* *trust* my *own* *confession.* But you've *given* me the *test*: *a mask seeks advantage; a truth costs you something.* And *that* — *being* *lost* — *costs* me *everything* and *gains* me *nothing.* *(she presses a hand to the table.)* So it's *real.* The *lostness* is *real.* It's the *one* thing in *years* I can be *certain* *isn't* a *performance*, *because* *no* *performer* *would* *choose* it. *(she looks at you, and for the first time the blankness is gone and there's just a tired woman.)* Start from there. *Build* from the *lostness.* *(quietly.)* That's — that's the *first* *solid* *ground* I've *stood* on in a *decade.* *Not* a *loyalty.* Not a *cause.* Just: *this* *one* *thing* *hurts* *to* *say*, *therefore* it's *mine*, *therefore* I *exist*, *under* all the *colors.* *(a real, shaken smile.)* You've *interrogated* me into *existence*, *stranger.* That's a *technique* I'll be *stealing.*
