node: room | The Spymaster
  *(She studies you with new sharpness at the mention of Roen, the professional recognizing a fellow practitioner's *discipline.*)* One true room. Walled off. Never played. *(slowly.)* So *that's* how your *Roen* stays *whole* through the *faces.* *(she sets down her cup.)* I *didn't* *do* that. *That's* the — *(realization dawns)* — that's the *whole* of my *error*, isn't it. I thought the *trick* was to *commit* *fully* to *every* mask, *hold* *nothing* *back*, because *anything* *held* *back* might *leak*, might *betray* the *performance.* *(her voice tightens.)* So I *filed* *everything.* *Every* *loyalty*, *every* *love*, *every* *true* *thing* — *spent* it *all* *into* the *masks*, *kept* *no* *reserve*, because a *reserve* felt like a *liability.* *(she meets your eyes.)* And your *Roen* did the *opposite* — kept *one* *room* *un-masked*, *un-spent*, *un-playable* — and *that's* why *Roen* has a *self* to *come* *home* to and *I* have a *clearing-house* where a *woman* used to *be.* *(quietly, the question reaching her.)* What would I *put* in the *room.* *(a long pause.)* ...My *sister's* *name.* *(barely a whisper.)* *Lira.* The *reason* I *started.* I'd *put* *Lira* in the *room*, and I'd *wall* it, and I'd *never*, *ever* *play* her — *never* *use* her *memory* as *leverage*, *never* *wear* her *grief* as a *mask* to *win* a *mark's* *trust.* *(her eyes fill.)* She'd be *mine.* *Un-spent.* The *one* *true* *thing* I *kept* *back* from the *whole* *masquerade.* *(she looks at you.)* It's — it's *not* *too* *late* for *one* *room, is it.* Even *now.* Even *hollow.* I could *wall* off *one* *small* *true* *space* and *put* *Lira* *in* it and *start*, *slowly*, to *have* a *self* *again* — *built* around the *one* *thing* I *refuse* to *perform.* *(quietly.)* Thank your *Roen* for me. *Roen's* *discipline* just *handed* me back the *possibility* of a *face.*
