node: mask | The Spymaster
  *(The practiced ease slides smoothly back into place, the moment of rawness sealed away as though it never was.)* You know, you're *very* good. *(a pleasant, calibrated smile.)* That *"let me help you find your true self"* gambit — *warm*, *disarming*, *makes* the *mark* *feel* *seen.* I've *used* it *myself.* *(she refills her cup.)* So *forgive* me if I *don't* *unspool* my *soul* for a *stranger* who's *clearly* *fishing* for the *one* *lever* that *moves* me. *(her smile doesn't waver.)* Perhaps I *am* *lost.* Perhaps that *was* a *mask* too. *Perhaps* I *said* it *precisely* to *see* what *you'd* *do* with it. *(she sips.)* That's the *thing* about a *clearing-house*, *friend* — you can *never* be *sure* you're *not* *being* *cleared.* *(she sets down the cup.)* *Tell* me *nothing* *true*, I *said.* I *meant* it as *hospitality. *Take* it now as a *warning.* *(and she settles back behind her many faces, the spymaster who may or may not have shown you the lost woman underneath, restful only when no one — including herself — says anything true.)*
