node: close | The Spymaster
  *(The spymaster settles back behind her layered faces in the dim of the safehouse — the woman who became every loyalty so fully that she wore away the one beneath them all — and whether you led her back to the sister the whole masquerade began for, or named her hollowness as hard-won disillusionment, or interrogated her into the one confession too costly to be a play, you carry away the last shadow's warning, which is the loop's warning in another key: that a self spent entirely into the roles it performs wears away like a handled coin, and that the only way to survive wearing a thousand faces is to wall off one small true room and refuse, whatever it costs, to ever play what's inside it.)*
